                <h1 class="title block" id="page-title">What is the Forum for? </h1>                
        <div id="breadcrumb" class="grid-full"><h2 class="element-invisible">You are here</h2><div class="breadcrumb"><a href="/">Home</a> » <a href="/about-college">About the College</a> » <a href="/about-college/writing-st-edmund-hall">Writing</a> » <a href="/about-college/hall-writers-forum" title="Hall Writers&#039; Forum">Hall Writers&#039; Forum</a> »</div></div>   
        
                
        
          <div class="region region-content">
    
<div id="block-system-main" class="block block-system">

    
  <div class="content">
    <div id="node-2369" class="node node-inside-page clearfix" about="/about-college/what-forum" typeof="sioc:Item foaf:Document"><div class="inner">
  
      <span property="dc:title" content="What is the Forum for? " class="rdf-meta element-hidden"></span>
  
  <div class="content">
    <span class="print-link"></span><div class="field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden"><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even" property="content:encoded"> <h3 style="border: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 4px; padding: 0px; font-family: 'segoe ui', Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif, 'Lucida Sans', 'lucida Sans Unicode';"><span style="font-size: 12px;">What is the forum for, and who is eligible to join? </span></h3><p style="border: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 1em; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7em; color: rgb(17, 17, 17); font-family: 'segoe ui', Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif, 'Lucida Sans', 'lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size: 12.8000001907349px;"><span style="border: 0px; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Verdana, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 16.7999992370605px; background-color: rgb(248, 248, 248);">The <a href="http://forum.seh.ox.ac.uk/index.php" style="border: 0px; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-decoration: none; color: rgb(166, 8, 20); transition: all 250ms ease-in-out; -webkit-transition: all 250ms ease-in-out;">Hall Writers’ Forum </a>was founded by <a href="https://www.seh.ox.ac.uk/about-college/lucy-newlyn" style="border: 0px; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-decoration: none; color: rgb(166, 8, 20); transition: all 250ms ease-in-out; -webkit-transition: all 250ms ease-in-out;">Lucy Newlyn</a> and <a href="https://www.seh.ox.ac.uk/about-college/stuart-estell" style="border: 0px; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-decoration: none; color: rgb(166, 8, 20); transition: all 250ms ease-in-out; -webkit-transition: all 250ms ease-in-out;">Stuart Estell </a>with a view to fostering dialogue, creative writing, and collaboration. Stuart is a former student of Lucy's, and they began planning the forum after a Hall Reunion for Aularians who had read English; but from the outset the idea was to include all members of the college's diverse community.</span></p><p style="border: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 1em; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7em; color: rgb(17, 17, 17); font-family: 'segoe ui', Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif, 'Lucida Sans', 'lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size: 12.8000001907349px;"><span style="border: 0px; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Verdana, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 16.7999992370605px; background-color: rgb(248, 248, 248);">They launched the Forum on line at the <a href="https://www.seh.ox.ac.uk/about-college/celebration-writing-hall" style="border: 0px; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-decoration: none; color: rgb(166, 8, 20); transition: all 250ms ease-in-out; -webkit-transition: all 250ms ease-in-out;">Hall Writers' Day in 2013.</a> Its members include current and former students of St Edmund Hall, members of the Hall's academic and non-academic staff, and <a href="http://forum.seh.ox.ac.uk/viewtopic.php?f=30&amp;t=91" style="border: 0px; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-decoration: none; color: rgb(166, 8, 20); transition: all 250ms ease-in-out; -webkit-transition: all 250ms ease-in-out;">associates from outside the college who have been nominated by forum members.</a></span></p><p style="border: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 1em; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7em; color: rgb(17, 17, 17); font-family: 'segoe ui', Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif, 'Lucida Sans', 'lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size: 12.8000001907349px;"><strong style="font-size: 12.8000001907349px; line-height: 1.7em;">What kind of writing does the forum encourage?</strong></p><p style="border: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 1em; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7em; color: rgb(17, 17, 17); font-family: 'segoe ui', Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif, 'Lucida Sans', 'lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size: 12.8000001907349px;"><span style="font-family: Verdana, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; line-height: 16.7999992370605px; background-color: rgb(248, 248, 248);">The Forum caters for all forms of writing, not just those traditionally described as ‘creative’. It is particularly keen to encourage new writing, </span><a href="http://forum.seh.ox.ac.uk/viewforum.php?f=25" style="font-family: Verdana, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; line-height: 16.7999992370605px; border: 0px; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-decoration: none; color: rgb(166, 8, 20); -webkit-transition: all 250ms ease-in-out; transition: all 250ms ease-in-out;">cross-disciplinary discussion</a><span style="font-family: Verdana, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; line-height: 16.7999992370605px; background-color: rgb(248, 248, 248);">, and the exchange of ideas across generations. Readers who do not consider themselves to be writers are welcome to comment, criticise, and enter into debate. </span></p><p style="border: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 1em; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7em; color: rgb(17, 17, 17); font-family: 'segoe ui', Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif, 'Lucida Sans', 'lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size: 12.8000001907349px;"><span style="font-family: Verdana, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; line-height: 16.7999992370605px; background-color: rgb(248, 248, 248);">Most of the site is open to public view; but we do have one section that is reserved for Forum Members, where we can 'workshop' writing in progress or discuss matters that are specially relevant to the college's community. This is the most popular and active part of the forum, where writers are posting material on a daily basis. Its seclusion is important: some Magazines don't accept work that has already been published, and many of the people posting in this section are working towards publication.</span></p><p style="border: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 1em 80px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7em; color: rgb(17, 17, 17); font-family: 'segoe ui', Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif, 'Lucida Sans', 'lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size: 12.8000001907349px;"><a href="https://www.seh.ox.ac.uk/about-college/how-forum-works"><span style="font-size: 12.8000001907349px; line-height: 1.7em;">Click here to find out how the forum works</span></a></p><p style="border: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 1em; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7em; color: rgb(17, 17, 17); font-family: 'segoe ui', Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif, 'Lucida Sans', 'lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size: 12.8000001907349px;"> </p><h3 style="border: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 1em; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.7em; color: rgb(17, 17, 17); font-family: 'segoe ui', Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif, 'Lucida Sans', 'lucida Sans Unicode'; font-size: 12.8000001907349px;"> </h3> </div></div></div>  </div>

  
  
</div></div>
  </div>
</div>  </div>
        
